.TH GM64 1 "25th September 2019" "PUPS build tools" "PUPS build tools"

.SH NAME
GM64 \- switch gcc compiler output model to 64 bits on x86_64 and aarch64 architectures 
.br

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gm64 
.B
[-usage | -help
] | {
.B -verbose
]
>& <log file>
.br

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gm64(1)
is a utility which switches the output model for a gcc compiler running on x86_64
compliant Intel architecture or aarch64 complaint ARM architecture from 32 to 64 bits.
.br


.SH OPTIONS

.B -usage | -help
display help and copyright information for the
.I gm64(1)
utility.
.br

.B -verbose
toggle
.B verbose
mode (error and status information is logged to
.I standard error
).
.br

.SH FILES

.B $HOME/.gccMultiMode.cf
and
.B /usr/bin/gccMultiMode.cf
which contains the current output mode flag, that is either
.B -m32
or
.B -m64
for Intel or
.B -mabi=ilp32
or
.B -mabi=lp64
for ARM. If the local file exists, it is used in preference to the global one.
.br

.B /usr/bin/gcc64
is the base (64 bit) gcc compiler. When
.I gm64(1)
is installed the existing (64 bit)
.B gcc
compiler
.B /usr/bin/gcc
is copied here.
.br

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
None.
